3. cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) - There is no direct connection to software development or programming in the paper, but the use of simulations and random matrix theory may be relevant to this sub-category. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses computational methods to calculate the economic impact of an epidemic, which falls under the scope of computational engineering and science. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper does not directly involve multiagent systems, but the concept of immunization can be seen as a strategy for multiple agents to prevent the spread of infection.
